., PNAS 2025; prebiotic guanidinylation with cyanamide suggested but not demonstrated."}, {"id": "rxn_008", "name": "Citrulline + NH\u2083 \u2192 Arginine (transamidation analogue)", "inputs": ["mol_010", "mol_002"], "outputs": ["mol_008"], "environment": "Biochemical", "agents": ["montmorillonite", "null"], "conditions": {"temperature": "320-350K", "pressure": "ambient", "catalyst": "montmorillonite", "aqueous": true, "other": "Wet-dry cycle, possible"}, "mechanism": "Conversion of citrulline to arginine through transamidation with NH\u2083.", "reasoning": "Speculative, follows metabolic logic (Glavin et al., 2025); not demonstrated prebiotically."}, {"id": "rxn_009", "name": "Strecker analog (5-carbon carbonyl + NH\u2083 + HCN \u2192 Arg \u03b1-aminonitrile)", "inputs": ["mol_001", "mol_002", "mol_013"], "outputs": ["mol_008"], "environment": "Surface", "agents": ["montmorillonite", "null"], "conditions": {"temperature": "320-350K", "pressure": "ambient", "catalyst": "montmorillonite", "aqueous": true, "other": "Wet-dry cycle, possible"}, "mechanism": "Strecker synthesis with putative 5-carbon carbonyl, NH\u2083 and HCN yields Arg \u03b1-aminonitrile.", "reasoning": "Miller (1986) and subsequent work: Not observed experimentally; included here for completeness as speculative."}, {"id": "rxn_010", "name": "CO + NH\u2083 + H\u2082S \u2192 HCN/Cyanamide (FeS hydrothermal catalysis)", "inputs": ["mol_013", "mol_002", "mol_014"], "outputs": ["mol_001", "mol_004"], "environment": "Hydrothermal", "agents": ["FeS", "greigite"], "conditions": {"temperature": "350-400K", "pressure": "high", "catalyst": "FeS, greigite", "aqueous": true, "other": "Reducing vent conditions"}, "mechanism": "FeS catalyzes reduction of CO with NH\u2083 and H\u2082S to yield HCN and cyanamide.", "reasoning": "Huber & Wachtershauser (1997); FeS/greigite catalysis produces key cyanosulfidic feedstock (Patel et al. 2015)."}, {"id": "rxn_011", "name": "Urea formation: NH\u2083 + CO\u2082 \u2192 Urea (hydrothermal catalysis)", "inputs": ["mol_002", "mol_013"], "outputs": ["mol_011"], "environment": "Hydrothermal", "agents": ["magnetite", "greigite"], "conditions": {"temperature": "350-400K", "pressure": "high", "catalyst": "magnetite, greigite", "aqueous": true, "other": "Alkaline vent conditions"}, "mechanism": "NH\u2083 reacts with CO\u2082 on magnetite/greigite producing urea.", "reasoning": "Analogous to prebiotic nitrogen cycles; supported by findings that urea is plausible (Miller 1986, Pol et al. 2022)."}], "pathways": [{"pathway_id": "P1", "name": "Cyanosulfidic Homologation Pathway (Patel et al. 2015)", "description": "HCN + acetylene forms acrylonitrile; NH\u2083 yields beta-aminopropionitrile; cyanamide and UV-driven reduction forms guanidinium intermediate; HCN homologation yields alpha-aminonitrile; hydrolysis gives arginine.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_001", "rxn_002", "rxn_003", "rxn_004", "rxn_005"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_005", "mol_006", "mol_004"]}, {"pathway_id": "P2", "name": "Glutamate\u2013Ornithine\u2013Citrulline\u2013Arginine Metabolic Analogue", "description": "Glutamate reductively aminated to ornithine; guanidinylation with cyanamide yields citrulline; transamidation with NH\u2083 to arginine.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_006", "rxn_007", "rxn_008"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_012", "mol_009", "mol_010"]}, {"pathway_id": "P3", "name": "Strecker Analogue Pathway", "description": "HCN, NH\u2083, and hypothetical 5-carbon carbonyl undergo Strecker reaction giving alpha-aminonitrile, hydrolyzed to Arg.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_009", "rxn_005"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_001", "mol_008"]}, {"pathway_id": "P4", "name": "Hydrothermal Feedstock Cyanosulfidic Pathway", "description": "FeS/Greigite catalyzed formation of HCN and cyanamide; these feed into surface pathway as per P1.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_010", "rxn_001", "rxn_002", "rxn_003", "rxn_004", "rxn_005"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_001", "mol_004"]}, {"pathway_id": "P5